A woman who was travelling as a passenger in a car has died in a crash in Surrey.The crash involving a grey Mercedes E220 happened in Buxton Lane, Caterham, before 03:00 BST.A 34-year-old woman died at the scene while two other passengers, a man and a woman in their 30s, were injured.A fourth occupant of the car fled the scene, police said.
The two injured passengers were taken to hospital, and the woman is in a life-threatening condition.Their next of kin have been informed and are being supported, police said.The person who fled the scene is described as a white man, aged between 30 and 40 and of stocky build. He was seen wearing a white t-shirt and carrying a small bag, police added.Road closures are in place at the Salmons Lane West roundabout while investigations continue.â€œWe ask you try and avoid the area as these closures will be in place for several hours today," a police spokesman said.Any witnesses or those with information about the crash is urged to contact police.
